<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-508-596  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 508 596.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Engineering Times  May 14 1990 n590 p26(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Computer net gets priority: White House hot on $1.9B program.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Robinson, Brian.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The $1.9 billion Federal High Performance Computing Program,intended to boost high-performance computing technology andknow-how in the US, is a current hot button for the BushAdministration, with great interest being taken in the project bythe President, Chief of Staff John Sununu, and director of theOffice of Management and Budget Richard Darman.andP;  A recent meetingof the President's Council of Advisors on Science and Technologywas given over almost entirely to the issue and Pres Bush hasproposed the formation of a new advisory committee specificallyfor the program.andP;  The core of the program is the construction of anationwide network linking most of the nation's companies,colleges and schools to large supercomputers and databases.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     GovernmentTechnologyNetworksNational Government.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>